'''''Tommy Cooper: Not Like That, Like This''''' is a 2014 television film, made by [[Left Bank Pictures]], about British comedian [[Tommy Cooper]].<ref>{{cite news 
 |url=http://www.comedy.co.uk/guide/tv/tommy_cooper_not_like_that/
 |title=Tommy Cooper: Not Like That, Like This
 |accessdate=1 May 2014
 |publisher=comedy.co.uk
}}</ref> 

==Plot==
The film focuses on the life of the late [[Tommy Cooper]], the popular [[British people|British]] comedian, and the dilemma he faced when he fell in love with his assistant Mary Kay. At the time he was married to Gwen, whom he affectionately nicknamed ''Dove''. Tommy was unable to choose between the two women and embarked upon a dual relationship that would last for 17 years. Cooper died during a live TV recording of ''[[Live from...|Live from Her Majesty's]]'' in front of millions of television viewers on 15 April 1984.<ref>{{cite news 
 |url=http://www.itvmedia.co.uk/tommy-cooper
 |title=Tommy Cooper
 |accessdate=30 April 2014
 |publisher=itv.com
}}</ref>

